auctex (9.9o-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream version.  (Closes: #32122)
  * update-auctex-elisp: Removed emacs' option `-no-site-file', since we
    already byte compile stuff without it.  This should allow AUC TeX to
    make good use of the `custom' add-on package with `emacs19'; however,
    it may well have some nasty side effects on non-standard sites, since
    this way we're going to compile things in an (potentially) unknown
    environment, due to the fact we let `site-start.el' to be loaded on
    startup as well.  Well, we'll see; thanks to Martin Stjernholm for
    this fix.  (Closes: #30419)

